      "))) ("[$] BPF meets io_uring" "Over the last couple of years, a lot of development effort has gone into
two kernel subsystems:
<a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/740157/\">BPF</a> and
<a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/810414/\">io_uring</a>.  The BPF virtual machine allows
programs from user space to be safely run within the context of the kernel,
while io_uring addresses the longstanding problem of running system calls
asynchronously.  As the two subsystems expand, it was inevitable that the
two would eventually meet; the first encounter happened in mid-February
with <a
href=\"https://lwn.net/ml/io-uring/cover.1613563964.git.asml.silence@gmail.com/\">this patch
set</a> from Pavel Begunkov adding the ability to run BPF programs from
within io_uring." "https://lwn.net/Articles/847951/rss" (24641 8482) old 15 nil nil ((guid nil nil) (title nil "[$] BPF meets io_uring") (link nil "https://lwn.net/Articles/847951/rss") (date nil "2021-03-04T18:04:18+00:00") (creator nil "corbet") (description nil "
      Over the last couple of years, a lot of development effort has gone into
two kernel subsystems:
<a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/740157/\">BPF</a> and
<a href=\"https://lwn.net/Articles/810414/\">io_uring</a>.  The BPF virtual machine allows
